dochttx (0.3.1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Implement teletext simulation (dochttx -d /dev/null).
  * Improve typography in the manual page.
  * Improve error handling.
  * Add basic test suite.
  * Set https://github.com/jwilk/dochttx/issues as bug report URL in the
    configure script.

 -- Jakub Wilk <jwilk@jwilk.net>  Fri, 22 Feb 2019 21:55:38 +0100

dochttx (0.3) unstable; urgency=low

  * Render G1 Block Mosaic Set as braille patterns.
  * Add the -d option to select input device.
    https://github.com/jwilk/dochttx/issues/2
  * Add the -l option to select character set(s).
    Use LC_CTYPE to choose character set automatically.
    https://github.com/jwilk/dochttx/issues/3
  * Fix an out-of-bound read.
    https://github.com/jwilk/dochttx/issues/4
  * Don't hardcode color map.
    (This should fix color rendering in some cases.)
  * Allow hex digits in page numbers.
  * Don't allow subpages 80 and above.
  * Improve Polish typography.
  * Improve documentation:
    + Add README.
    + Add SVG screenshot.
    + Put license into a separate file.
    + Add manual page.
  * Require ncurses with wide-character support
  * Improve the build system:
    + Add install target.
    + Add check against BSD make.
      (Only GNU make is supported.)
    + Use pkg-config to query information about ncurses.
  * Improve error handling.

 -- Jakub Wilk <jwilk@jwilk.net>  Fri, 01 Feb 2019 18:19:34 +0100

dochttx (0.2.5) unstable; urgency=low

  * Use autoconf for the build system.
  * Stop requiring wide-character support in the ncurses library.
    (It's still strongly recommended.)
  * Improve error handling.

